I moved to LA a week ago. I’ve spent the last 3 years explaining to people why I lived an hour away from LA. It was mainly because I was extremely depressed and very scared. Over the last few months I went back to therapy, started taking the right meds, and repaired some very painful relationships that I felt were unrealistic to fix. I’ve really felt the world opening up to me again in the same way I did when I started this account when I was a teenager. I’ve grown such an amazing audience on Tik tok by just sharing my voice and I can’t explain how grateful I am.

After a week of living in Hollywood I feel like all the dreams I gave up on in those 3 years of depression feel a little more reachable. I really dwelled in the fact that since I slowed down creating content I lost the support of so many people I knew personally. Other creators spoke to me as if I was a has been or my success was a fluke and honestly for a couple years I just believed it. But making content is really like riding a bike- I think sometimes we can be so stuck in our bad mental health cycles that we forget how much of our lives and personalities it takes away. 

I’m sharing this in hopes that if you feel like you’re not good enough, your dreams that seemed to be coming so easy to you stopped feeling reachable, you’re scared to take that risk, it’s seriously okay. Taking your time to be in the right mindset is what is most important, it won’t feel good if you force it. I love you! I’m excited for this next chapter

Reawakening 🪷 

Shot by @celinakenyon

I am not a before or after photo, I’m enough being me in all forms ♥️ After struggling with my body image and weight gain from a 2 year depressive episode, I’ve been learning how to love myself again after such a long time. 

So many of you were there with me on my journey of recovering from restrictive eating and I just felt like a failure when I found myself suffering from disordered eating once again on the other end of the spectrum. I still have such a long way to go but the last 5 months have been so amazing. After taking my mental health into my hands I can finally look in the mirror and see the person I remembered from 2 and a half years ago. 

So many people told me I looked better with the weight on but all I saw was someone who was so alone and wasn’t able to cope properly. I finally feel so much more comfortable in my body- I don’t feel pressured to look anything other than healthy. 

It took so much courage but I finally decided that it’s time for me to take new modeling digitals and apply for modeling agencies. I love being an influencer but being a model was always my goal, we deserve to see more South Indian women with realistic bodies on billboards. I know I’ve been silent for so many years but I’m asking for your support one more time 🤍

The wine bubbled up after the cork popped and only the wine that was exposed to areas that were heated boiled. It didn't ruin the wine, it was perfectly fine.

The entire process took 8 minutes and is completely safe. The glass would only shatter if it was exposed to a temp change

I’ve always felt so out of place everywhere I’ve lived. I loved growing up in Africa but it was so clear I wasn’t from there so people constantly asked me where I was from. In India my accent is a dead give away and people are constantly asking me where I’m from. Moving to America was hard and traumatic to say the least, and gaining an audience at the age of 15 was so isolating at times. I rarely speak about it but being accused of “buying my followers” and being made fun of for the content I posted back in my early days really did affect the way I view myself. 

Lately I’ve realized something has changed. It’s been around 6 months that I moved to LA and I think for the first time ever in my life I feel like I belong somewhere. I’ve met so many amazing people who have the same passions as me, I finally don’t have to over explain what I do anymore. People just get it. It feels so good. 

Anyways long story short- I’m happy.

Today means something to me ❤️‍🩹 And I wouldn’t be around to talk about it if it wasn’t for my amazing community. I used to complain that the decisions, choices and boundaries I had to make were so much harder than the people around me. But I never stopped to realize how strong the cards I was dealt has made me become. I started my platform in 2015 to share a raw and candid view on depression, anxiety, PTSD & having an ED. 8 years later I’m only just realizing how important this journey was for me to share, I could not do this alone. All of these pictures were posted on this account and so many of you lived through these life events with me without even realizing it. 

Even though I still share the hard parts of life people still think I have everything together. Recovery is not always a linear process, it has taken me almost a decade to get to this point, but I still slip up too. 

If you don’t think it’s worth it anymore, take it from someone who believed that there was nothing for me past 18- Life changes in a way you could never predict and sometimes it’s so effortless it’ll make you laugh at how impossible you thought it could be. 

I love you, and as always I truly am so happy you’re here 

Cas

I’m back in Mexico for the first time since, well I’m sure a lot of you guys know. I was really apprehensive to plan a trip coming back to Tulum, but I always knew I wanted to come back to this beautiful place to rewrite those awful memories with new ones. 

Over the last few months I’ve been learning to say yes more to things that make me uncomfortable. It’s such a huge step for me because for so long my mental state didn’t permit me to do anything that caused me to be anything other than in a neutral or relaxed state. When people think about mental illness they often over look the struggles behind recovering and putting the pieces back together because we are so focused on getting out of the holes and pitfalls of life. 

Like I’ve always encouraged, change is possible. Your mental illness does not need to limit you! It may take a few weeks or months (or years like it took me) but your mind can surprise you. 

I love you all so much, I’m only thinking about your support and kind words while I’m here in Mexico. I can’t wait to share more of these memories with you soon

Day 1 of making better memories in Mexico! 👙

social_posts.post_text:
For so long I would sit and compare my life to the people around me and wonder why *I* couldn’t leave my unhappy relationship, why couldn’t *I* heal my relationship with my family, why could *I* get a handle on my relationship with my body? 

For the last 3 years it felt like everyone had passed me and I was just floating in an anxious shallow puddle of these bad choices I made and maintained. I think a lot of people will agree that sometimes even if you want to change your life forcing it can definitely make it worse, there is nothing more frustrating than living life being self aware of your mistakes and short comings and not having the mental strength or be in the right situation to change it. 

In the middle of 2023 I decided that I was finally strong enough to have every hard conversation I had been preparing myself to have. I distanced myself from people who I called family and confronted issues with my actual family. I made the choice to pick myself for genuinely it feels like the first time ever. I did all of these hard things with the intention of coming out on the other side completely alone. But wow I was so wrong!!!!! Leaving my unhealthy relationship opened up my life to a healthy one. Distancing myself from friends that were unstable and toxic helped me strengthen friendships that I already had and being honest with my family has helped me feel a lot more understood. 

Anxiety is such a powerful emotion and the way it can completely blind you from reality is so scary. I am ended 2023 with so much love and happiness. All of the questions I would ask myself over and over again I have all the answers to now. 

If you’re feeling stuck and discouraged about the choices you’re made- it’s not too late to change them and pick yourself first ♥️ I’m ready to have to make hard decisions and have hard conversations in 2024, I hope you are too!
